         <component>
            <section>
               <id root="db826c62-2ced-4d6e-a96f-da9a5de79747"/>
               <code code="34089-3" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="DESCRIPTION SECTION"/>
               <title>
  Silicone Tape
</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>Silicone Tape</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Uses<br/>• To be applied to wounds or scars as a protective silicone barrier.<br/>• As a dressing for abrasions, surgical 

wounds, donor sites, lacerations, ulcers, skin tears, superficial partial thickness burns, venous leg ulcers.<br/>• As a dressing/securement for IV 

related uses, pressure ulcers, skin care, and wound care</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Precautions<br/>• Do not use if you are allergic to silicone<br/>• Keep out of reach of children</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Directions for use<br/>• Apply tape to wound or scar as needed or as directed by your physician. Remove tape, wash area, and 

apply new tape at least every 24 hours.</paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20160203"/>
            </section>
         </component>
